<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4141] Looks like Serializing cache broken in 1.1</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4141</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I get the following error while setting the row cache to be 1500 MB&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;INFO 23:27:25,416 Initializing row cache with capacity of 1500 MBs and provider org.apache.cassandra.cache.SerializingCacheProvider&lt;br/&gt;
java.lang.OutOfMemoryError: Java heap space&lt;br/&gt;
Dumping heap to java_pid26402.hprof ...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;havent spend a lot of time looking into the issue but looks like SC constructor has &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;.initialCapacity(capacity)&lt;br/&gt;
.maximumWeightedCapacity(capacity)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; which 1500Mb&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
