                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13252084" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Thu, 12 Apr 2012 00:22:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;attached fixes this issue... changes to ConcurrentLinkedHashCache is not needed but thought the default was good instead of setting it to 0.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13252311" author="xedin" created="Thu, 12 Apr 2012 09:51:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Wouldn&apos;t that instead crash with OOM later in some unpredictable moment (e.g. when cache is read from disk) or when cache resizing is done?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13252452" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Thu, 12 Apr 2012 14:23:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;initialCapacity here is the number of elements in the hashmap and not the size. Size should be controlled by maximumWeightedCapacity (yes the names are confusing through)&lt;br/&gt;
We are running OOM because we where trying to allocate 1500 * 1024 *1024 elements.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the intial capacity is used to create the ConcurrentHashMap&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ConcurrentHashMap&amp;lt;K, Node&amp;gt;(builder.initialCapacity, 0.75f, concurrencyLevel);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13252461" author="xedin" created="Thu, 12 Apr 2012 14:37:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13252499" author="vijay2win@yahoo.com" created="Thu, 12 Apr 2012 15:39:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
